{"title_page": "Prosper Grech", "text_new": "{{short description|Maltese Catholic cardinal}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type = cardinal\n| honorific-prefix = His Eminence\n| name = Prosper Grech\n| honorific-suffix = [[Augustinians|OSA]]\n| title = Cardinal Deacon of Santa Maria Goretti\n| image = Cardinal Grech 2014.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| alt = \n| caption = Cardinal Grech in 2014\n| church = \n| archdiocese = \n| province = \n| metropolis = \n| diocese = \n| see = \n| elected = \n| appointed = \n| term = \n| term_start = \n| quashed = \n| term_end = \n| predecessor = \n| opposed = \n| successor = \n<!---------- Orders ---------->\n| ordination = 25 March 1950\n| ordinated_by = \n| consecration = 8 February 2012\n| consecrated_by = [[Paul Cremona]]\n| cardinal = 18 February 2012\n| created_cardinal_by = [[Pope Benedict XVI|Benedict XVI]]\n| rank = [[Cardinal deacon]]\n| other_post = {{unbulleted list|Titular Archbishop of [[San Leone (see)|San Leone]] (2012)}}\n<!---------- Personal details ---------->\n| birth_name = Stanley Grech\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1925|12|24|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Birgu|Vittoriosa]], [[Crown Colony of Malta]]\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2019|12|30|1925|12|24|df=yes}}\n| death_place = [[Rome]], [[Italy]]\n| buried = \n| nationality = [[Malta|Maltese]]\n| religion = Roman Catholic\n| residence = \n| parents = \n| spouse = \n| children = \n| occupation = \n| profession = \n| alma_mater = {{unbulleted list|[[Pontifical Gregorian University]]|[[Pontifical Biblical Institute]]|[[University of Fribourg]]|[[University of Oxford]]|[[University of Cambridge]]}}\n| motto = {{lang|la|In te Domine speravi}}<br>('In you, Lord, I take refuge'; {{Bibleverse|Psalm|71:1}})\n| signature = \n| signature_alt = \n| coat_of_arms = \n| coat_of_arms_alt = \n<!---------- Other ---------->\n| other = \n}}\n{{Infobox cardinal styles |\n    name=Prosper Grech|image=Coat of arms of Prospero Grech.svg|\n    dipstyle=[[His Eminence]] |\n    offstyle=[[Your Eminence]] |\n    relstyle=[[Cardinal]] |\n    deathstyle= |}}\n'''Prosper Grech''' {{post-nominals|list=[[Augustinians|OSA]]}} (24 December 1925 \u2013 30 December 2019) was a Maltese [[Augustinians|Augustinian]] friar, who co-founded the [[Patristic Institute Augustinianum]] in Rome. He was created a [[Cardinal (Catholic Church)|cardinal]] by [[Pope Benedict XVI]] on 18 February 2012. He was the second Maltese member of the [[College of Cardinals]], the first since 1843.{{efn|The first was [[Fabrizio Sceberras Testaferrata]] (1757-1843).<ref name=\"Malta Today\"/>}}\n\n==Formation and studies==\nBorn Stanley Grech in [[Vittoriosa]], [[Malta]], on 24 December 1925, he studied at the Lyceum.<ref name=\"Times of Malta\">{{cite web |url= http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20120106/local/pope-appoints-maltese-cardinal.401247 |title=Pope to appoint Maltese Cardinal|publisher= Times of Malta|date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref> He took the name Prospero when he joined the [[Augustinian Order]] in 1943.<ref name=death/> While Malta was under siege during the [[Second World War]], Grech served as a gunner in the [[Royal Malta Artillery]].<ref name=\"Vatican Radio\">{{cite web |url= http://www.radiovaticana.org/en1/Articolo.asp?c=563410 |title=Cardinal Prosper Grech:'in te Domini speravi' |first=Veronica |last=Scarisbrick|publisher= Vatican Radio |date= 16 February 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref> He was ordained to the priesthood at the [[Basilica of Saint John Lateran]] in [[Rome]]<ref name=vaticanbio/> on 25 March 1950.<ref name=OR2012/> \n\nGrech studied philosophy at St. Mark's Priory, [[Rabat, Malta]], and [[theology]] in St. Monica's College, Rome. He earned a doctorate in theology at the [[Gregorian University]], Rome (1953), obtained a licentiate in sacred scripture from the [[Pontifical Biblical Institute]], Rome (1954), and a diploma in educational psychology from [[University of Fribourg]], Switzerland (1951). Grech conducted research in [[Semitic languages]] at the universities of [[University of Oxford|Oxford]] (1957\u201358) and [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] (1958\u201359).<ref name=\"Malta Today\">{{cite web |url= http://www.maltatoday.com.mt/en/newsdetails/news/national/Maltese-theologian-to-be-appointed-Cardinal-201216 |title=Maltese theologian to be appointed Cardinal |first= Matthew|last=Vella |work=Malta Today |date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Teaching==\nIn 1959, Grech was appointed lecturer at the Augustinian Theological College, Rabat. He also served as professor at the [[Augustine Institute]] and joined the staff of the [[Vicar General for Vatican City]].<ref name=\"Times of Malta\"/> As secretary to the Vicar General, Bishop [[Petrus Canisius Van Lierde]], who was sacristan of the Apostolic Palace,<ref name=mattei>{{cite interview | url = http://www.30giorni.it/articoli_id_78290_l3.htm | date= 1 February 2012 | title= Interview with Cardinal Prosper Grech by Paolo Mattei | publisher = 30 Giorni }}</ref> his duties included dressing [[Pope John XXIII]] and [[Pope Paul VI]] for liturgical functions. During the [[Papal conclave, 1963|1963 Papal conclave]], he heard Giovanni Battista Montini's confession a couple of hours prior to his election as Pope Paul VI.<ref name=\"Vatican Radio\"/> In 1970, together with Fr. Agostino Trap\u00e8, Grech founded the [[Patristic Institute Augustinianum]] attached to the [[Lateran University]] in Rome<ref name=\"Times of Malta\"/> and served as its president from 1971 to 1979.<ref name=OR2012/> He was a member of the [[Studiorum Novi Testamenti Societas]] (SNTS);<ref name=vaticanbio/> he became a member of the [[Pontifical Academy of Theology]] in 2003 and of the [[Pontifical Biblical Commission]] in 2004.<ref name=OR2012/>\n\nGrech lectured on [[hermeneutics]] for over thirty years at the [[Pontifical Biblical Institute]] in Rome.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lucie-Smith |first1=Alexander |title=Father Prospero, possibly the most intelligent man alive, is to become Malta\u2019s second ever cardinal | date= 9 January 2012 |url=https://catholicherald.co.uk/commentandblogs/2012/01/09/father-prospero-possibly-the-most-intelligent-man-alive-is-to-become-malta\u2019s-second-ever-cardinal/ |newspaper= Catholic Herald |accessdate=7 October 2019}}</ref> He became a consultor to the [[Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith]] in 1984 and went to India on behalf of the congregation as an [[apostolic visitor]] of seminaries in 1998.<ref name=OR2012>{{cite news | access-date = 2 January 2020 | date= 19 February 2012 | url = http://www.osservatoreromano.va/en/news/new-cardinals-created-by-benedict-xvi | title= New cardinals created by Benedict XVI | work = L'Osservatore Romano }}</ref>\n\nGrech authored various articles and publications and presented lectures on the Bible, hermeneutics and patristics.<ref>{{cite web |title=An insightful lecture by Cardinal Prospero Grech OSA |url=https://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2013-11-10/letters/an-insightful-lecture-by-cardinal-prospero-grech-osa-3131670534/ |newspaper= The Malta Independent |accessdate=12 October 2019}}</ref> On 13 December 2011, he was appointed a Companion of the National Order of Merit of the Republic of Malta.<ref name=\"Malta Today\"/>\n\n==Cardinal==\n[[Pope Benedict XVI]] announced on 6 January 2012 that he would create Grech a cardinal, together with 21 others, on 18 February 2012. <ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.ncronline.org/blogs/ncr-today/pope-names-22-new-cardinals-including-dolan-and-obrien | work = National Catholic Reporter | accessdate = 1 January 2020 | date = 6 January 2012 |title= Pope names 22 new cardinals, including Dolan and O'Brien | first = John L. |last=Allen Jr.}}</ref> He was the first Augustinian made a cardinal in 111 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://santagostinopavia.wordpress.com/2012/02/20/il-cardinale-grech-primo-agostiniano-nel-sacro-collegio-dopo-111-anni/|title=Il Cardinale Grech, primo agostiniano nel Sacro Collegio dopo 111anni |website=santagostinopavia.wordpress.com |accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nAs [[canon law]] requires cardinals to be bishops unless they receive special [[Dispensation (canon law)|dispensation]], Grech was consecrated a bishop on 8 February 2012 by [[Paul Cremona]], [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Malta|Archbishop of Malta]], assisted by Archbishop [[Giuseppe Versaldi]], and [[Mario Grech]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Gozo|Bishop of Gozo]].<ref>{{cite news | access-date = 1 January 2020 | url = https://knisja.mt/l-ordinazzjoni-episkopali-ta-mons-prospero-grech-arcisqof-titulari-ta-san-leone/ | date = 9 February 2012| language = mt | title = L-ORDINAZZJONI EPISKOPALI TA\u2019 MONS. PROSPERO GRECH \u2013 AR\u010aISQOF TITULARI TA\u2019 SAN LEONE | website = Archdiocese of Malta}}</ref> He took the episcopal motto {{lang|la|In te Domine speravi}} ('In you, Lord, I take refuge'), from the [[incipit|opening words]] of [[Psalm 71]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Episcopal ordination on February 8 | date= 21 January 2012 |url= https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20120121/local/episcopal-ordination-on-february-8.403249 |website=Times of Malta |publisher=Times of Malta |accessdate=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe was created a [[cardinal deacon]] by [[Pope Benedict XVI]] in a [[Papal consistory|consistory]] on 18 February 2012 and assigned the [[titular church]] of [[Santa Maria Goretti, Rome|Santa Maria Goretti]].<ref name=vaticanbio>{{cite web| accessdate = 6 December 2017| title= Grech Card. Prosper, O.S.A. |publisher= Holy See Press Office | url= https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/documentation/cardinali_biografie/cardinali_bio_grech_p.html | url-status=live | archive-date= 4 May 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170904105112/http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/documentation/cardinali_biografie/cardinali_bio_grech_p.html }}</ref> Grech delivered the opening meditation at the [[2013 papal conclave]], but his age prevented him from participating as an elector.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wooden |first1=Cindy |title=Cardinal urged Church unity in speech to conclave before Francis\u2019s election | date= 8 August 2013 |url=https://catholicherald.co.uk/news/2013/08/08/cardinal-urged-church-unity-in-speech-to-conclave-before-franciss-election/ |newspaper= Catholic Herald |accessdate=8 October 2019}}</ref> He warned that the Church was always threatened by disunity: \"Between ultra-traditionalist extremists and ultra-progressive extremists, between priests rebelling against obedience and those who don't recognize the signs of the times, there always will be the risk of small schisms that not only damage the church, but go against the will of God.\" He raised the issue of how the Church hierarchy was handling the sexual abuse crisis: \"Today many people are not able to come to believe in Christ because his face is obscured or hidden behind an institution that lacks transparency.\"<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.ncronline.org/news/vatican/maltese-cardinal-patristic-scholar-dies-94 | access-date = 1 January 2020 | date= 31 December 2019 | title= Maltese cardinal, patristic scholar, dies at 94 | agency = Catholic News Service | first = Cindy | last = Wooden | work= National Catholic Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | access-date = 1 January 2020 | title = Acta Apostolicae Sedis | url = https://www.vatican.va/archive/aas/documents/2013/aprile-maggio2013.pdf | date= April-May 2013 | volume= CV | pages= 352\u20137 }}</ref> When Pope Francis marked the 50th anniversary of the founding of the Augustinianum, he praised Grech for the \"grandiose simplicity\" his sermons had achieved in his old age.<ref>{{cite news | work= Zenit | access-date = 1 January 2020 | date= 17 February 2019 | url = https://zenit.org/articles/pope-to-augustinianum-be-faithful-to-your-roots-and-to-your-task/ | title = Pope to Augustinianum: Be Faithful to Your Roots and to Your Task }}</ref>\n\nGrech died in Rome's Santo Spirito Hospital on 30 December 2019.<ref name=death>{{cite news | url = https://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2019-12-30/local-news/Cardinal-Prospero-Grech-dies-6736217915 | access-date = 31 December 2019 | date= 30 December 2019 | title = Cardinal Prospero Grech dies | newspaper = The Malta Independent }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vaticannews.va/en/church/news/2019-12/cardinal-prosper-grech-dies-augustinian.html|title=Cardinal Prosper Grech dies suddenly in Rome |publisher= Vatican News| first= Bernadette Mary |last=Reis |access-date = 31 December 2019 |date=30 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n;Additional sources \n* Rafael Lazcano, ''Episcopologio agustiniano''. Editorial Agustiniana, Guadarrama (Madrid), 2014, vol. I, p. 364-386.\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web| accessdate = 6 December 2017| title= Grech Card. Prosper, O.S.A. |publisher= [[Holy See Press Office]] | url= https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/documentation/cardinali_biografie/cardinali_bio_grech_p.html | url-status=live | archive-date= 4 May 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170904105112/http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/documentation/cardinali_biografie/cardinali_bio_grech_p.html }}\n\n{{portal bar|Biography|Catholicism|Malta}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grech, Prosper}}\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Maltese theologians]]\n[[Category:Maltese Roman Catholic bishops]]\n[[Category:Maltese cardinals]]\n[[Category:Augustinians]]\n[[Category:Hermeneutists]]\n[[Category:Pontifical Biblical Institute alumni]]\n[[Category:Patristic Institute Augustinianum]]\n[[Category:Cardinals created by Pope Benedict XVI]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic titular archbishops]]\n[[Category:Pontifical Gregorian University alumni]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the National Order of Merit (Malta)]]\n[[Category:Pontifical Biblical Institute faculty]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Maltese Catholic cardinal}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type = cardinal\n| honorific-prefix = His Eminence\n| name = Prosper Grech\n| honorific-suffix = [[Augustinians|OSA]]\n| title = Cardinal Deacon of Santa Maria Goretti\n| image = Cardinal Grech 2014.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| alt = \n| caption = Cardinal Grech in 2014\n| church = \n| archdiocese = \n| province = \n| metropolis = \n| diocese = \n| see = \n| elected = \n| appointed = \n| term = \n| term_start = \n| quashed = \n| term_end = \n| predecessor = \n| opposed = \n| successor = \n<!---------- Orders ---------->\n| ordination = 25 March 1950\n| ordinated_by = \n| consecration = 8 February 2012\n| consecrated_by = [[Paul Cremona]]\n| cardinal = 18 February 2012\n| created_cardinal_by = [[Pope Benedict XVI|Benedict XVI]]\n| rank = [[Cardinal deacon]]\n| other_post = {{unbulleted list|Titular Archbishop of [[San Leone (see)|San Leone]] (2012)}}\n<!---------- Personal details ---------->\n| birth_name = Stanley Grech\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1925|12|24|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Birgu|Vittoriosa]], [[Crown Colony of Malta]]\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2019|12|30|1925|12|24|df=yes}}\n| death_place = [[Rome]], [[Italy]]\n| buried = \n| nationality = [[Malta|Maltese]]\n| religion = Roman Catholic\n| residence = \n| parents = \n| spouse = \n| children = \n| occupation = \n| profession = \n| alma_mater = {{unbulleted list|[[Pontifical Gregorian University]]|[[Pontifical Biblical Institute]]|[[University of Fribourg]]|[[University of Oxford]]|[[University of Cambridge]]}}\n| motto = {{lang|la|In te Domine speravi}}<br>('In you, Lord, I take refuge'; {{Bibleverse|Psalm|71:1}})\n| signature = \n| signature_alt = \n| coat_of_arms = \n| coat_of_arms_alt = \n<!---------- Other ---------->\n| other = \n}}\n{{Infobox cardinal styles |\n    name=Prosper Grech|image=Coat of arms of Prospero Grech.svg|\n    dipstyle=[[His Eminence]] |\n    offstyle=[[Your Eminence]] |\n    relstyle=[[Cardinal]] |\n    deathstyle= |}}\n'''Prosper Grech''' {{post-nominals|list=[[Augustinians|OSA]]}} (24 December 1925 \u2013 30 December 2019) was a Maltese [[Augustinian]] friar, who co-founded the [[Patristic Institute Augustinianum]] in Rome. He was created a [[Cardinal (Catholic Church)|cardinal]] by [[Pope Benedict XVI]] on 18 February 2012. He was the second Maltese member of the [[College of Cardinals]], the first since 1843.{{efn|The first was [[Fabrizio Sceberras Testaferrata]] (1757-1843).<ref name=\"Malta Today\"/>}}\n\n==Formation and studies==\nBorn Stanley Grech in [[Vittoriosa]], [[Malta]], on 24 December 1925, he studied at the Lyceum.<ref name=\"Times of Malta\">{{cite web |url= http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20120106/local/pope-appoints-maltese-cardinal.401247 |title=Pope to appoint Maltese Cardinal|publisher= Times of Malta|date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref> He took the name Prospero when he joined the [[Augustinian Order]] in 1943.<ref name=death/> While Malta was under siege during the [[Second World War]], Grech served as a gunner in the [[Royal Malta Artillery]].<ref name=\"Vatican Radio\">{{cite web |url= http://www.radiovaticana.org/en1/Articolo.asp?c=563410 |title=Cardinal Prosper Grech:'in te Domini speravi' |first=Veronica |last=Scarisbrick|publisher= Vatican Radio |date= 16 February 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref> He was ordained to the priesthood at the [[Basilica of Saint John Lateran]] in [[Rome]]<ref name=vaticanbio/> on 25 March 1950.<ref name=OR2012/> \n\nGrech studied philosophy at St. Mark's Priory, [[Rabat, Malta]], and [[theology]] in St. Monica's College, Rome. He earned a doctorate in theology at the [[Gregorian University]], Rome (1953), obtained a licentiate in sacred scripture from the [[Pontifical Biblical Institute]], Rome (1954), and a diploma in educational psychology from [[University of Fribourg]], Switzerland (1951). Grech conducted research in [[Semitic languages]] at the universities of [[University of Oxford|Oxford]] (1957\u201358) and [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] (1958\u201359).<ref name=\"Malta Today\">{{cite web |url= http://www.maltatoday.com.mt/en/newsdetails/news/national/Maltese-theologian-to-be-appointed-Cardinal-201216 |title=Maltese theologian to be appointed Cardinal |first= Matthew|last=Vella |work=Malta Today |date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Teaching==\nIn 1959, Grech was appointed lecturer at the Augustinian Theological College, Rabat. He also served as professor at the [[Augustine Institute]] and joined the staff of the [[Vicar General for Vatican City]].<ref name=\"Times of Malta\"/> As secretary to the Vicar General, Bishop [[Petrus Canisius Van Lierde]], who was sacristan of the Apostolic Palace,<ref name=mattei>{{cite interview | url = http://www.30giorni.it/articoli_id_78290_l3.htm | date= 1 February 2012 | title= Interview with Cardinal Prosper Grech by Paolo Mattei | publisher = 30 Giorni }}</ref> his duties included dressing [[Pope John XXIII]] and [[Pope Paul VI]] for liturgical functions. During the [[Papal conclave, 1963|1963 Papal conclave]], he heard Giovanni Battista Montini's confession a couple of hours prior to his election as Pope Paul VI.<ref name=\"Vatican Radio\"/> In 1970, together with Fr. Agostino Trap\u00e8, Grech founded the [[Patristic Institute Augustinianum]] attached to the [[Lateran University]] in Rome<ref name=\"Times of Malta\"/> and served as its president from 1971 to 1979.<ref name=OR2012/> He was a member of the [[Studiorum Novi Testamenti Societas]] (SNTS);<ref name=vaticanbio/> he became a member of the [[Pontifical Academy of Theology]] in 2003 and of the [[Pontifical Biblical Commission]] in 2004.<ref name=OR2012/>\n\nGrech lectured on [[hermeneutics]] for over thirty years at the [[Pontifical Biblical Institute]] in Rome.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lucie-Smith |first1=Alexander |title=Father Prospero, possibly the most intelligent man alive, is to become Malta\u2019s second ever cardinal | date= 9 January 2012 |url=https://catholicherald.co.uk/commentandblogs/2012/01/09/father-prospero-possibly-the-most-intelligent-man-alive-is-to-become-malta\u2019s-second-ever-cardinal/ |newspaper= Catholic Herald |accessdate=7 October 2019}}</ref> He became a consultor to the [[Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith]] in 1984 and went to India on behalf of the congregation as an [[apostolic visitor]] of seminaries in 1998.<ref name=OR2012>{{cite news | access-date = 2 January 2020 | date= 19 February 2012 | url = http://www.osservatoreromano.va/en/news/new-cardinals-created-by-benedict-xvi | title= New cardinals created by Benedict XVI | work = L'Osservatore Romano }}</ref>\n\nGrech authored various articles and publications and presented lectures on the Bible, hermeneutics and patristics.<ref>{{cite web |title=An insightful lecture by Cardinal Prospero Grech OSA |url=https://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2013-11-10/letters/an-insightful-lecture-by-cardinal-prospero-grech-osa-3131670534/ |newspaper= The Malta Independent |accessdate=12 October 2019}}</ref> On 13 December 2011, he was appointed a Companion of the National Order of Merit of the Republic of Malta.<ref name=\"Malta Today\"/>\n\n==Cardinal==\n[[Pope Benedict XVI]] announced on 6 January 2012 that he would create Grech a cardinal, together with 21 others, on 18 February 2012. <ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.ncronline.org/blogs/ncr-today/pope-names-22-new-cardinals-including-dolan-and-obrien | work = National Catholic Reporter | accessdate = 1 January 2020 | date = 6 January 2012 |title= Pope names 22 new cardinals, including Dolan and O'Brien | first = John L. |last=Allen Jr.}}</ref> He was the first Augustinian made a cardinal in 111 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://santagostinopavia.wordpress.com/2012/02/20/il-cardinale-grech-primo-agostiniano-nel-sacro-collegio-dopo-111-anni/|title=Il Cardinale Grech, primo agostiniano nel Sacro Collegio dopo 111anni |website=santagostinopavia.wordpress.com |accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nAs [[canon law]] requires cardinals to be bishops unless they receive special [[Dispensation (canon law)|dispensation]], Grech was consecrated a bishop on 8 February 2012 by [[Paul Cremona]], [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Malta|Archbishop of Malta]], assisted by Archbishop [[Giuseppe Versaldi]], and [[Mario Grech]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Gozo|Bishop of Gozo]].<ref>{{cite news | access-date = 1 January 2020 | url = https://knisja.mt/l-ordinazzjoni-episkopali-ta-mons-prospero-grech-arcisqof-titulari-ta-san-leone/ | date = 9 February 2012| language = mt | title = L-ORDINAZZJONI EPISKOPALI TA\u2019 MONS. PROSPERO GRECH \u2013 AR\u010aISQOF TITULARI TA\u2019 SAN LEONE | website = Archdiocese of Malta}}</ref> He took the episcopal motto {{lang|la|In te Domine speravi}} ('In you, Lord, I take refuge'), from the [[incipit|opening words]] of [[Psalm 71]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Episcopal ordination on February 8 | date= 21 January 2012 |url= https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20120121/local/episcopal-ordination-on-february-8.403249 |website=Times of Malta |publisher=Times of Malta |accessdate=12 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe was created a [[cardinal deacon]] by [[Pope Benedict XVI]] in a [[Papal consistory|consistory]] on 18 February 2012 and assigned the [[titular church]] of [[Santa Maria Goretti, Rome|Santa Maria Goretti]].<ref name=vaticanbio>{{cite web| accessdate = 6 December 2017| title= Grech Card. Prosper, O.S.A. |publisher= Holy See Press Office | url= https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/documentation/cardinali_biografie/cardinali_bio_grech_p.html | url-status=live | archive-date= 4 May 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170904105112/http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/documentation/cardinali_biografie/cardinali_bio_grech_p.html }}</ref> Grech delivered the opening meditation at the [[2013 papal conclave]], but his age prevented him from participating as an elector.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wooden |first1=Cindy |title=Cardinal urged Church unity in speech to conclave before Francis\u2019s election | date= 8 August 2013 |url=https://catholicherald.co.uk/news/2013/08/08/cardinal-urged-church-unity-in-speech-to-conclave-before-franciss-election/ |newspaper= Catholic Herald |accessdate=8 October 2019}}</ref> He warned that the Church was always threatened by disunity: \"Between ultra-traditionalist extremists and ultra-progressive extremists, between priests rebelling against obedience and those who don't recognize the signs of the times, there always will be the risk of small schisms that not only damage the church, but go against the will of God.\" He raised the issue of how the Church hierarchy was handling the sexual abuse crisis: \"Today many people are not able to come to believe in Christ because his face is obscured or hidden behind an institution that lacks transparency.\"<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.ncronline.org/news/vatican/maltese-cardinal-patristic-scholar-dies-94 | access-date = 1 January 2020 | date= 31 December 2019 | title= Maltese cardinal, patristic scholar, dies at 94 | agency = Catholic News Service | first = Cindy | last = Wooden | work= National Catholic Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | access-date = 1 January 2020 | title = Acta Apostolicae Sedis | url = https://www.vatican.va/archive/aas/documents/2013/aprile-maggio2013.pdf | date= April-May 2013 | volume= CV | pages= 352\u20137 }}</ref> When Pope Francis marked the 50th anniversary of the founding of the Augustinianum, he praised Grech for the \"grandiose simplicity\" his sermons had achieved in his old age.<ref>{{cite news | work= Zenit | access-date = 1 January 2020 | date= 17 February 2019 | url = https://zenit.org/articles/pope-to-augustinianum-be-faithful-to-your-roots-and-to-your-task/ | title = Pope to Augustinianum: Be Faithful to Your Roots and to Your Task }}</ref>\n\nGrech died in Rome's Santo Spirito Hospital on 30 December 2019.<ref name=death>{{cite news | url = https://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2019-12-30/local-news/Cardinal-Prospero-Grech-dies-6736217915 | access-date = 31 December 2019 | date= 30 December 2019 | title = Cardinal Prospero Grech dies | newspaper = The Malta Independent }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vaticannews.va/en/church/news/2019-12/cardinal-prosper-grech-dies-augustinian.html|title=Cardinal Prosper Grech dies suddenly in Rome |publisher= Vatican News| first= Bernadette Mary |last=Reis |access-date = 31 December 2019 |date=30 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n;Additional sources \n* Rafael Lazcano, ''Episcopologio agustiniano''. Editorial Agustiniana, Guadarrama (Madrid), 2014, vol. I, p. 364-386.\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web| accessdate = 6 December 2017| title= Grech Card. Prosper, O.S.A. |publisher= [[Holy See Press Office]] | url= https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/documentation/cardinali_biografie/cardinali_bio_grech_p.html | url-status=live | archive-date= 4 May 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170904105112/http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/documentation/cardinali_biografie/cardinali_bio_grech_p.html }}\n\n{{portal bar|Biography|Catholicism|Malta}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grech, Prosper}}\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Maltese theologians]]\n[[Category:Maltese Roman Catholic bishops]]\n[[Category:Maltese cardinals]]\n[[Category:Augustinians]]\n[[Category:Hermeneutists]]\n[[Category:Pontifical Biblical Institute alumni]]\n[[Category:Patristic Institute Augustinianum]]\n[[Category:Cardinals created by Pope Benedict XVI]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic titular archbishops]]\n[[Category:Pontifical Gregorian University alumni]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the National Order of Merit (Malta)]]\n[[Category:Pontifical Biblical Institute faculty]]\n", "name_user": "BD2412", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Fixinglinks to disambiguation pages, replaced:Augustinian\u2192Augustinian", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prosper_Grech"}
